The government has declared Monday January 2 a public holiday.Interior CS Joseph Nkaissery made the announcement through a gazette notice to the effect that New Year falls on a Sunday.Section 4 of Public Holidays Act 2011 states that when a public holiday falls on a Sunday, the following day is treated as a holiday.The constitution defines three national holidays under Section 9. These are Madaraka Day, marked on June 1, Mashujaa Day on October 20, and Jamhuri Day on December 12.Kenyans also got a chance to rest on December 27 since the Christmas and Boxing Day fell on Sunday and Monday respectively.Read: State declares December 27 a holiday